Isolation Comments: isolated in 1985 in California, USA, during an outbreak of listeriosis among patients with AIDS
Comments: Listeria monocytogenes strain 4b F2365. This strain was isolated in 1985 in California, USA, during an outbreak of listeriosis among patients with AIDS. The strain is of serotype 4b and was isolated from a cheese product that caused the outbreak.

Isolation Source: sporadic human listeriosis case, is a representative of ribotype DUP-1042B
Isolation Comments: isolated from a sporadic human listeriosis case, is a representative of ribotype DUP-1042B
Comments: Listeria monocytogenes FSL J1-194. This serotype 1/2b strain, isolated from a sporadic human listeriosis case, is a representative of ribotype DUP-1042B. This ribotype has been linked to two human listeriosis outbreaks and is also responsible for a number of sporadic human listeriosis outbreaks. This strain is being sequenced for comparative genome analysis.

Isolation Comments: isolated from a single case of human listeriosis in 1989 linked to consumption of processed meat
Comments: Listeria monocytogenes F6900.This serotype 1/2a strain was isolated from a single case of human listeriosis in 1989 linked to consumption of processed meat. This strain is being sequenced for comparative genome analysis.

Isolation Comments: isolated from food associated with a case in a human listeriosis outbreak in 2000 linked to consumption of sliced turkey
Comments: Listeria monocytogenes J2818. This serotype 1/2a strain was isolated from food associated with a case in a human listeriosis outbreak in 2000 linked to consumption of sliced turkey. This is one of the few lineage II strains associated with human listeriosis. This strain is being sequenced for comparative genome analysis.

Isolation Source: case of febrile gastrointestinal illness among students and staff who had eaten at one of two school cafeterias
Isolation Comments: isolated from a case of febrile gastrointestinal illness among students and staff who had eaten at one of two school cafeterias in Northern Italy in 1997
Comments: Listeria monocytogenes HPB2262. This serotype 4b strain was isolated from a case of febrile gastrointestinal illness among students and staff who had eaten at one of two school cafeterias in Northern Italy in 1997. This strain is being sequenced for comparative genome analysis.
